The paper deals with the complexity theory of LCL problems in the LOCAL model of computation on toroidal 2-dimensional grids. This involves the study of distributed algorithms and graph theory, which are typically covered in the cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) sub-categories. The paper also discusses colourings and orientations of graphs, which fall under the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. Finally, the paper involves the design and automation of algorithms, which is relevant to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category.
